-2025", "topic": "DC-DC Converters", "impact": "Under steady-state conditions, the voltage and current waveforms of a dc-dc converter can be found by use of two basic circuit analysis principles. The principle of inductor volt-second balance states that the average value, or dc component, of voltage applied across an ideal inductor winding must be zero", "beneficiaries": "II Year EIE students ", "resource_person": "Dr. Sanjay kumar Limaji Patil, Professor, Department of Instrumentation & Control and Dean Alumni and International Relations, College of Engineering, Shivajinagar, Pune.", "participants_count": "80"}, {"dates": "28-01-2026", "topic": "From Sensors to Systems : Foundations of Embedded Design ", "impact": "Learnt about Foundations of Embedded Design through Sensors to systems", "beneficiaries": "III Year EIE-B Section Students", "resource_person": "Dr. Veena N. Hegde, Professor in the Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering at B.M.S. College of Engineering, Bengaluru", "participants_count": "65"}, {"dates": "28-01-2026", "topic": "Importance of Control Systems   &  Process Control Systems", "impact": "Learnt about Basics of Control systems like Batch processes, Continuous Processes, Discrete Processes and Operational Constraints. ", "beneficiaries": "II Year EIE students ", "resource_person": "Dr. K.Narashima Rao, Retired Professor in the Department of Electronics and Instrumentation Engineering at B.M.S. College of Engineering, Bengaluru", "participants_count": "70"}], "events_conducted": [{"event_type": "Guest Lecture", "description": "Guest Lecture is organized for III B. Tech EIE- I & II section Students on “Process Control Automation” by Prof. Sudhir D. Agashe, Department of Instrumentation and Control, COEP Technological University.  On 31-12-2025 from 10.00AM to 01.00PM in Room No.C-203. 70 students and 2 faculty members attended."}, {"event_type": "Guest Lecture", "description": "Guest Lecture is organized for II B. Tech EIE- I & II