324	5	2	2026	{"guest_lectures": [{"dates": "02-02-2026", "topic": "From Continuous-time to Discrete-time: Illustration with a simple circuit", "impact": "The guest lecture titled “From Continuous-time to Discrete-time: Illustration with a Simple Circuit” was organized to provide undergraduate students with a strong conceptual understanding of the transition from continuous-time signals to discretetime signals, which forms the foundation of digital signal processing. The lecture explained the practical and theoretical aspects of sampling using simple circuit illustrations, making abstract concepts easier to visualize and understand. The resource person discussed real-world relevance, highlighting how continuous-time physical signals are converted into discrete-time representations for digital processing systems. Emphasis was placed on the importance of sampling, discretization, and system VALLURUPALLI NAGESWARA RAO VIGNANA JYOTHI INSTITUTE OF ENGINEERING AND TECHNOLOGY An Autonomous Institute Vignana Jyothi Nagar, Pragathi Nagar, Nizampet (S.O.), Hyderabad – 500 090, TS, India. modeling in modern communication and signal processing applications. The interactive session encouraged students to ask questions, enabling them to connect classroom theory with practical implementation. Overall, the lecture enriched students’ knowledge and strengthened their fundamentals in signal processing.", "beneficiaries": "II B.Tech ECE students ", "resource_person": "Subrata Bhattacharya, Retired faculty member, ECE Department, IIT(ISM) Dhanbad – 826004, Jharkhand ", "participants_count": "45"}, {"dates": "04-02-2026", "topic": "Engineering the Future: 6G, Innovation, and Your Role", "impact": "", "beneficiaries": "III B.Tech students", "resource_person": "Amit Kumar Karna ,Lead – 6G Product Innovation | Scientist ‘E’, C-DOT ", "participants_count": "80"}, {"dates": "21-02-2026", "topic": "Engineering - Science = Trial and error; Science - Engineering = Philosophy", "impact": "", "bene