ers", "description": "Brief orientation on ACE Scholarship Test (AST).  for II ECE students(190) by on 02-02-2026.  availing scholarships through the Students were informed that the AST will be conducted on 1st March 2026 and can help them secure financial support for competitive exam preparation. They were advised to refer to the shared document for details and circulate this information in their respective student social media groups.  "}, {"event_type": "Guest Lecture", "description": "Guest lecture for III B.Tech students(80) on  “Engineering the Future: 6G, Innovation, and Your Role” by    Amit Kumar Karna ,Lead – 6G Product Innovation | Scientist ‘E’, C-DOT on 04-02-2026."}, {"event_type": "Workshop", "description": "Workshop on Unified Technical Hybrid  for IV Year Students of ECE, EIE, EEE by Dr M Vishnu Prasad, Strategic HR Division Head, UTS. Mr M Ravi, UTS on 12th & 13th February,2026. This workshop discussed about the Core Electrical & Electronics Job Mela 2026 successfully provided students with valuable technical exposure, industry insights, and employment opportunities. The initiative helped participants understand real-world engineering practices, develop job-relevant technical skills, and prepare effectively for core industry careers."}, {"event_type": "Guest Lecture", "description": "\\tECE department in association with IEEE VNRVJIET SB Chapter organizing a guest lecturer for I B.Tech ECE (160) and EIE students (56) on “Engineering - Science = Trial and error; Science - Engineering = Philosophy!  By Dr. B. Satyanarayana, DAE Raja Ramanna Chair, Tata Institute of Fundamental Research, Hyderabad on 21-02-2026"}, {"event_type": "Guest Lecture", "description": "ECE department organizing a guest lecture for III ECE-C Students (45) on “Applications, Advancements and Test cases of 6G” on   by Mr. K.Ram Mohan Rao on 21-02-2026"}], "events_organized": [{"dates": "13-02-2026", "topic": "Training Program on Design of Finite State machines using Verilog HDL", "impact": "The session concluded with an interactive discussion where students raised questions regarding timing closure challenges, synthesis constraints, FPGA implementation aspects, and career opportunities in front-end and back-end VLSI design. The resource person addressed the queries with practical examples from industry experience.\\nThe training program was highly informative and enhanced the students’ understanding of FSM design and timing analysis concepts, which are critical for careers in VLSI design and semiconductor industries\\n", "beneficiaries": "III B.Tech ECE students", "resource_person": "Mr K Viresh from IISC Bangalore ,Nuatlabs", "participants_count": "50"}, {"dates": "02-02-2026 ", "topic": "ACE Scholarship Test (AST)", "impact": "Availing scholarships through the Students were informed that the AST will be conducted on 1st March 2026 and can help them secure financial support for competitive exam preparation. They were advised to refer to the shared document for details and circulate this information in their respective student social media groups", "beneficiaries": "II ECE students", "resource_person": "Dinesh Kumar, Asst. Manager, ACE Engg. Academy", "participants_count": "190"}, {"dates": "12th & 13th February, 2026", "topic": "Unified Technical Hybrid Workshop - UTS", "impact": "The Unified Technical Hybrid Workshop and the Core Electrical & Electronics Job Mela 2026 successfully provided students with valuable technical exposure, industry insights, and employment opportunities. The initiative helped participants understand real-world engineering practices, develop job-relevant technical skills, and prepare effectively for core industry careers", "beneficiaries": "IV ECE students ", "resource_person": "Workshop on Dr M Vishnu Prasad, Strategic HR Division Head, UTS. Mr M Ravi, UTS", "participants_count": "37"}, {"dates": "20-02-2026", "topic": "Training Program on Analog IC Design using CADENCE tools ", "impact": "The objective of the program was to provide students with practical exposure to analog IC design methodologies and hands-on understanding of circuit design using CADENCE tools, which are essential for careers in Analog and Mixed-Signal VLSI design.\\nThe session began with a detailed explanation of MOS differential amplifiers, including operating principles, biasing techniques, small-signal analysis, differential gain, CMRR, and device sizing considerations. The speaker demonstrated schematic design and simulation of a differential amplifier using the CADENCE Virtuoso environment, enabling students to understand real-time design flow and performance evaluation through DC, AC, and transient analysis\\n", "beneficiaries": "III-Year B.Tech ECE & I- M.Tech VLSI System Design students", "resource_person": "Mr. Md. Abdul Haseeb, Junior Analog Design Engineer, Lemon Flip Solutions ", "participants_count": "25"}], "industrial_visits": [{"date": "13-02-2026", "year": "II B.Tech ECE-A", "count": "45", "impact": "Akshaya Patra. Akshaya Patra contributes to policy dialogue and sectoral advocacy. On the ground, it runs capacity building initiatives for cook-cum-helpers (CCHs), enhancing safety, quality and efficiency in school lunch programme across the country. In times of crisis, Akshaya Patra has stepped up to provide critical support. In collaboration with the Government, the National Disaster Response Force (NDRF) and other stakeholders, the Foundation supported the survivors in Kerala, Andhra Pradesh and Assam with timely and essential food relief services as they recovered and rebuilt. 5 faculty and 58 students visited to this industrial visit.", "industry": "Akshaya Patra Foundation", "location": "Kandi–Shankarpalli Road, Opposite RTA Office, Kandi, Sangareddy, Hyderabad"}, {"date": "20-02-2026", "year": "II B.Tech ECE-C", "count": "46", "impact": "Akshaya Patra. Akshaya Patra contributes to policy dialogue and sectoral advocacy. On the ground, it runs capacity building initiatives for cook-cu